title: Sidewall, "West St. Mary's Manor", 1935–45
description: Design composed of flowing bands simulating lace and ribbons after style of Louis XV. Within medallions are shapes of leaves and flowers. Original from old house at Williamsburg. This is an approved Colonial Williamsburg reproduction. Drop repeat. Printed in margin: "Katzenbach and Warren, West St. Mary's Manor; Made in U.S.A. 311 run 1 Union Made."

tombstone.epitaph:
Sidewall, "West St. Mary's Manor", 1935–45.
1935–45. Machine-printed. Gift of William E. Katzenbach. 1946-18-4.
